00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Welcome many people here who have not attended a program of Shri Mataji Nimala Devi.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:20.000
By good fortune we are holding a seminar here this weekend and we had the idea to open it out to a wider public

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:30.000
to share with you the remarkable discovery which is Sahaja Yoga.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:59.000
Shri Mataji Nimala Devi is an absolutely unique figure in this world and people have come from many European countries to join us this weekend.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:25.000
I am going to ask Gregor de Calvamattin who is a Swiss national who has written a book on the subject of Shri Mataji's advent

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:39.000
to make a presentation before Shri Mataji arrives to give you some orientation.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Why it is that this is such a unique opportunity for all of us at this juncture in our history, in the national history, in the international history, in the very evolution of our species.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:27.000
You may hear some big words this evening but I hope that you are people of a calibre to seek the reality, the truth in big words

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:40.000
and not to be satisfied with superficial answers to sublime questions.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:49.000
We have been having an intensely joyful seminar.

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:53.000
We want to share that joy with you.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:03:00.000
There is a very specific way by which that joy can be shared by everyone.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.000
It is the birthright of everyone.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:10.000
It is nothing especially abnormal.

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:18.000
Everyone has the potential within them to achieve what has been promised.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:48.000
We have very much that later on you will make a point of finding out for yourself individually how much potential you have to transform into the promised state.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:58.000
Which is very blissful, very peaceful and very nourishing.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:04.000
Which we call Self-realization.

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:19.000
After the program, those who are interested to do so may like to leave their name and address with us in the foyer so that we can be in touch with you about other programs.

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:30.000
Programs are held regularly in London and in many other cities in this country and we look forward to meeting you and getting to know you.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:40.000
Without further ado, I will ask Gregor to speak to you and to introduce Remar to you who will be here in a few minutes.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:09.000
All right, it is working.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:15.000
Again, good evening to everybody and most welcome.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:18.000
It is a very nice surroundings.

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:21.000
We had a very jolly weekend here.

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:24.000
We thank you for coming this evening.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:39.000
Now, introducing Sahaja Yoga or Shri Mataji is always a privilege although it is not a very easy topic.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:06:03.000
The reason it is not an easy topic is that the subject matter is slightly beyond the borders of our wildest dreams and while presenting it we have to be very careful not to look like somebody who would be naive to the point of idiosity.

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:05.000
Is it an English word, idiosity?

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:07.000
Okay.

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:11.000
Because what we are talking about is self-realization.

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:18.000
If any of us know what self-realization is about then we know it is a very big thing.

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:36.000
It is something that very few saints and sages of the older days used to achieve after lives of tremendous labors and penances dedicated to that very purpose which obviously is not the situation in which I am finding myself.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
I am an international civil servant, a wife, three children and so on.

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:45.000
So that keeps me pretty busy.

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:52.000
So self-realization while living in the world, this sounds like utopia.

00:06:52.000 --> 00:07:00.000
I have met Shri Mataji about 10 years ago, slightly more as a person.

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:05.000
And that is enough for me to know it is not utopia, it is reality.

00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:17.000
Now I have no pretension to communicate this very truth to you because if I have accepted it, it is on the basis of my own experience and not because anybody would tell me so.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:24.000
Actually the people who told me so, I told them that they were, you know, kidding themselves.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:34.000
And I would expect from you the same kind of healthy scepticism, i.e. you shouldn't believe me of course.

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:47.000
Somebody who believes people in this world today is somebody who is in for troubles because especially in the field of spirituality, you have all kinds of crazy show going on in town.

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:50.000
Unfortunately these shows are sometimes very successful.

00:07:50.000 --> 00:08:03.000
So that for someone who is genuine but confused, which seems to be the characteristic of many seekers, certainly, I mean, I would certainly describe myself as being confused.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:09.000
When I think about the state I was before, I met Shri Mataji.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:21.000
It's very difficult to know who is genuine and who is not, who delivers the goods and who doesn't, and who is just a kind of illusion makers.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:35.000
So the way to go about this riddle is just to submit to you that whatever may be said on Sahaja Yoga is for you an hypothesis.

00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:39.000
And this is probably what Shri Mataji will tell you also in a few minutes.

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:51.000
Now, you know that for an hypothesis to be considered as a law, it has to fulfill two requirements.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:56.000
It has to be communicable and verifiable under certain conditions.

00:08:56.000 --> 00:09:07.000
So the hypothesis of Sahaja Yoga which is going to be led down or presented for you is going to be verified for those who sow desire, not for the others of course,

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:25.000
by a session of meditation at the end of the program of Shri Mataji, in which Shri Mataji will again show her absolutely amazing capacity to play this catalytical role in granting people their self-realization.

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:39.000
So if you came here to listen to a lecture, you'll like someone who came and thought he had five dollars in his pocket, but it's not five, it's five thousand dollars.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:49.000
Because really what you can get this evening is much more the analytical knowledge which is communicated by means of words.

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:54.000
So this is a kind of introduction to the hypothesis.

00:09:57.000 --> 00:10:16.000
And I assure you that the only thing it takes to verify what is actually going on is a certain intellectual honesty, that's all.

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:19.000
Certain genuineness.

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:24.000
And of course the desire to know what's going on.

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:30.000
Not about Sahaja Yoga of course, but what's going on about our own life, about the way to fulfill it.

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:35.000
Now the hypothesis is very simple.

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:38.000
This is the framework of the hypothesis.

00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:43.000
And what we say is this.

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:51.000
You have the sacrum bone which is more or less at the bottom of your spine.

00:10:51.000 --> 00:11:02.000
An energy which could be called in our tradition as the residual consciousness of the Holy Spirit in man.

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:07.000
This energy is called Kundalini in Sanskrit.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:19.000
Now what we call Self-Realization, that has to be defined, is the following process.

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:31.000
It's the process of this energy going up within the spine, crossing this famous point known as the third eye in various esoteric traditions.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:45.000
Going through this beautiful flower here which Lord Buddha described as the thousand petaled lotus.

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:50.000
And oozing out of the top of the skull.

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:57.000
Now when this takes place, what does it mean, what are the implications?

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.000
I think Shri Mataji is already coming.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:15.000
What are the implications of this process?

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:26.000
First of all, you can register the process in, I would say, essentially two ways.

00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:40.000
When the energy crosses this center, the Agnya Chakra, one enters into a state which is a state of silence.

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:49.000
Now we all know, we'd rather think a lot and it's not easy to stop thinking even if we wish to do so.

00:12:50.000 --> 00:13:02.000
This state of silence announces the quality of what Lord Jesus Christ has described as the Kingdom of God.

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:15.000
Because when one can penetrate farther into this silence, one undoubtedly discovers a new quality of being.

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:17.000
And I would like to come back on this.

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:26.000
Now once the Kundalini is just a couple of centimeters upwards and oozes out of the head, then what happens?

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:34.000
There again, what happens has been referred to in very ancient texts.

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:47.000
What actually happens is one feels the manifestation of something which is a cool breeze.

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:57.000
And this is a cool breeze which was called as Pneuma onus by the Greek fathers of the church.

00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:15.000
It was referred to also in the Bible as this mighty wind which erupted in the house where the apostles were gathered for Pentecost.

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:23.000
There are many references in various cultures to this phenomenon that we call vibrations.

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:31.000
What actually happens is that our central nervous system, which means this physical system by which we feel sensations,

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:39.000
becomes aware of a subtle energy which was always existing before but which we could not perceive.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:42.000
It's like you have, let's say, a radio here.

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:47.000
If the radio is not switched on, it cannot pick up all the waves.

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:55.000
And the music which is in the room in the same way, Self-realization, allows our central nervous system to pick on those waves,

00:14:55.000 --> 00:15:00.000
to feel these vibrations which are a spiritual energy.

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:13.000
In other words, this is the meeting point of matter and spirit because with the material structure, one becomes aware of spirit.

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:18.000
And this is a breakthrough into the fourth dimension.

00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:29.000
These vibrations are the category of perception that Kant was requiring in order to know the things in themselves,

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:32.000
in order to know reality.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:40.000
And it is because at that time he said that we don't have this new or this other category of perception

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:45.000
to know metaphysical realities, metaphysics, that is what is beyond physics.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:50.000
That is why we should just limit ourselves to rationality and from there on,

00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:59.000
the whole demarch, the whole direction of the Western seekers went into basically this finite world

00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:08.000
and no more this world which was keeping people like Plato and Socrates busy, the world of the things in themselves, of reality.

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:16.000
Now this is important to know because this breakthrough in our category of perception has been sought by so many seekers

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:24.000
that people who know that background, would it be only intellectually, know that one thing has to happen

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:29.000
in order to know reality is that we have to have a new means.

00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:37.000
And this is how you'll better understand the importance of these vibrations and the importance of what can be done with them.

00:16:37.000 --> 00:16:45.000
This is such a rich and vast topic that I simply would not like to enter into it now.

00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:54.000
Now going back to what I said a few minutes ago, this quality of silence one discovers at the level of the Agia Chakra

00:16:54.000 --> 00:17:00.000
is the space of reality between two thought movements.

00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:11.000
Now the action of this energy which we have called Kundalini pushes the thoughts on the side and then you enter in your own realm.

00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:19.000
What actually happens is this, is that once the Kundalini is at the top of the head,

00:17:19.000 --> 00:17:25.000
there is a secret link between the head and the heart.

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:33.000
And the heart is the seat of the self, the spirit, the Atma in Sanskrit.

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:43.000
So through this link in your consciousness, in your brain, you start imbibing Atma consciousness.

00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:51.000
That means you start being aware, conscious of those qualities which are the qualities of the self

00:17:51.000 --> 00:18:01.000
which are called Sat-Chit-Ananda meaning truth, consciousness and bliss.

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:13.000
So this is the hypothesis as short as I could.

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:24.000
This is true Shri Mataji.

00:18:51.000 --> 00:19:01.000
This is reading as our recipe.

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:17.000
Now as I mentioned, the very reassuring thing about Sahaja Yoga is that nobody is ever taught to believe in anything

00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:25.000
that is not object of experience and perception.

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:38.000
I also mentioned that for those who saw desire, the verification of the hypothesis can take place at the end of this program.

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:44.000
Now I should perhaps before ending tell you why it is so.

00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:52.000
Why it is that we who are very, I should say normal people,

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:57.000
why is it that we should be in a position to know this experience?

00:19:57.000 --> 00:20:00.000
What have we done to deserve it?

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:09.000
I mean if I ask this question for myself, I'm a bit puzzled because I certainly did not at any point

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:15.000
have got the feeling that I had done anything to deserve that.

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:26.000
So it came as such a surprise to me that I should get my realization that really for quite some time I would not quite believe that it is so.

00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:34.000
And I found out later on that many people have the same difficulty to relate to something which is so incredibly beyond our wildest dream

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:36.000
that it's just to go to be true.

00:20:36.000 --> 00:20:38.000
You know where is the catch? I mean it's not possible.

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:40.000
Well it is.

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:47.000
And Shimataji is a very, which I welcome here, very gracious of you to have come.

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:49.000
We thank you so much.

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:52.000
We certainly are very grateful to you for coming Shimataji.

00:20:56.000 --> 00:21:05.000
Shimataji is a very poetical, simple image which in my view is perfect because it carries the strength of simplicity and it says it all.

00:21:05.000 --> 00:21:15.000
Shimataji says that well if you have a tree which starts producing flowers in the middle of winter under snow and storm, this is a miracle.

00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:28.000
And that miracle where those great souls of the past which received their realization at a point where the whole evolutionary process was not quite mature for this.

00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:30.000
And therefore that will struggle in an incredible way.

00:21:30.000 --> 00:21:36.000
And this is what you learn when you study the lives of such great people.

00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:43.000
Now if this same tree is blossoming in spring, it's not a miracle.

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:48.000
It's nature's ways and rhythm.

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:51.000
It is the dance of evolution.

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:53.000
It is the moment that should happen.

00:21:53.000 --> 00:22:04.000
And so Shimataji says we now have entered a time where this process of triggering our mass self-realization has come.

00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:15.000
And if you study arts, literature, anything, any parameter of modern civilization, you know that there is a tremendous expectation for this kind of breakthrough.

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:27.000
And this is pretty obvious that today Englishmen for instance are not motivated by many things, certainly not by competing with Japanese in order to make gadgets.

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:33.000
I mean the economic indicators prove that they don't devote much energy to these things.

00:22:33.000 --> 00:22:39.000
So what do they care about?

00:22:39.000 --> 00:22:43.000
Cricket maybe but other things too.

00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:54.000
And actually I would submit that it is probably an evolutionary progress to accept that GNP should decrease because one does not bother about it.

00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:57.000
But then what should we devote our attention to?

00:22:57.000 --> 00:23:07.000
And many people in this country as in any so-called industrial countries are trying to devote more energy to the pursuit of this inner truth.

00:23:07.000 --> 00:23:19.000
The only trouble is the setup that I have described before is that there is such a big show in town that people don't go into the right shop.

00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:26.000
Because first of all they assume it has to be found in a shop where you can buy it and this is the first mistake.

00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:35.000
So here you can't buy because it's too expensive.

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:40.000
It's so expensive that it can only be given.

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:44.000
Trimata Gissel realization is as important as breathing.

00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:51.000
If you would have to puncture your bank account in order to have the right to breathe you would be dead long time back.

00:23:51.000 --> 00:23:56.000
And it is the same thing.

00:23:56.000 --> 00:24:02.000
So it happens now because now the time has come and it happens for another reason.

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:07.000
And this other reason if I may say so is sitting before you.

00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:22.000
Now speaking to I would say a few people who have never had exposure to Sahaja Yoga

00:24:22.000 --> 00:24:27.000
I should certainly keep a kind of sobriety while introducing Trimata Gissel which is difficult.

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:40.000
Because her achievements are so extraordinary that they are difficult to express in English which is a language appreciating understatements.

00:24:43.000 --> 00:24:46.000
It's very difficult to understate Trimata Gissel.

00:24:46.000 --> 00:24:49.000
I mean we are condemned to understate her anyway.

00:24:49.000 --> 00:24:56.000
But how to give some or end some justice to her labor.

00:24:56.000 --> 00:25:05.000
The work she has been doing in this country and I should say in the whole of Western Europe not to mention Australia and of course India.

00:25:08.000 --> 00:25:13.000
What I know is that she is a totally selfless, totally genuine person.

00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:21.000
Not only she didn't ever take any penny, I should blush for saying such nonsense from anybody.

00:25:21.000 --> 00:25:32.000
But the first lot of her followers in London were of such a kind of economically derelict soul that she had to pay for the rent of the flat for some time.

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:39.000
So this is one of the oddities of Sahaja Yoga and there are many others that you will discover in due time.

00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:52.000
Trimata Gissel despite a tremendous power that we would not be able to face if that power would not be just love.

00:25:52.000 --> 00:26:06.000
Despite cities, despite qualities that in my humble view are to be found in nobody on this earth and I have seen a lot of so-called spiritual people before I met Trimata Gissel.

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:17.000
Despite all this, she is extremely human. I mean much more than me, I am quite surprised about that.

00:26:23.000 --> 00:26:34.000
There is a word in Sanskrit for this and this word is called Mahamaya and Mahamaya means the Great Illusion.

00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:44.000
So you have the privilege to sit this evening in front of a very, very great illusion and this is the illusion that you are in front of a human being.

00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:56.000
It's a nice illusion though because if you would realize that it is not so, you may run away and this is not the purpose of the evening.

00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:14.000
So I suppose that I should end this few words by means of introduction.

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:33.000
Thanking you very much for having come all the way from wherever you came and if Sahaja Yoga is full of joy, is full of humor, it's also a sacred reality.

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:48.000
It is a sacred reality of our innermost divine being which opens itself if we in all humility and sincerity so wish.

00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:58.000
Trimata Gissel, I am again in the name of everybody most graceful that you should grace this evening.

00:27:58.000 --> 00:28:22.000
And it is my humblest prayer that everybody who has come should experience their Self-realization and what is even as important as that, should understand what great, great gift that evening is for them.

00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:24.000
Thank you very much.

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:31.000
Let's read a flower.

00:28:58.000 --> 00:29:14.000
I bow to all the seekers of truth.

00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:38.000
We had no intentions of having any public programs in England but somehow Mr. Gavin Brown hopes against hopes.

00:29:38.000 --> 00:30:05.000
And they spent lot of money for this program and I only feel sorry that every time they have a public program, we get very few people and even if you get last time we had about 300 people who were new, they got some of them did touch realization.

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:11.000
They looked very serious but nothing inside.

00:30:11.000 --> 00:30:27.000
We lost most of them because you see we have become used to our mental capacity to enact something and not to be the reality.

00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:37.000
It's a specialty of mental people that they talk too much, they say too much, have nothing with them.

00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:48.000
It's very shocking sometimes when you see how people say things about reality.

00:30:48.000 --> 00:30:59.000
I watch sometimes television, I see people on the television and I feel they are somewhere near reality, they are talking about reality.

00:30:59.000 --> 00:31:06.000
They understand that there's something missing in their lives and they are looking for it.

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:24.000
But when it comes to actualization and to achieving what you have, whatever is your own, they become absolutely mundane, frivolous, very surprising.

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:28.000
I can't understand why it should happen.

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:39.000
Now supposing you say, as God has been giving me certificates, great certificates is given and also he is a diplomat.

00:31:39.000 --> 00:31:50.000
So diplomatically he was trying to please all of you so that you take to Sahaja Yoga because he doesn't want you to commit the same mistakes that most of them have committed.

00:31:51.000 --> 00:31:58.000
But despite all that, let us face ourselves clearly.

00:32:00.000 --> 00:32:07.000
Newcomers are absolutely a minority here so I'm talking also to Sahaja Yoga.

00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:10.000
Let us face ourselves fully.

00:32:11.000 --> 00:32:14.000
Are we ourselves?

00:32:15.000 --> 00:32:31.000
We've got everything supposing we say, alright, we have seen the power of political achievement, of economic achievements, of other achievements which we call emotional achievements.

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:35.000
But have we really faced ourselves?

00:32:35.000 --> 00:32:37.000
Have we seen ourselves?

00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:39.000
What is our quality of life?

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:46.000
I asked an Englishman, I said, what is the quality of an Englishman?

00:32:46.000 --> 00:32:53.000
He said, it depends on how many times he goes for a sea resort, can you imagine?

00:32:53.000 --> 00:32:55.000
What?

00:32:55.000 --> 00:32:56.000
Sea resort.

00:32:56.000 --> 00:33:00.000
How many years back did you start going to the sea resort?

00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:03.000
I don't think we never heard about it in India.

00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:10.000
It's about twenty-five years back somebody's stupid fellow must be or somebody very clever maybe.

00:33:10.000 --> 00:33:17.000
Put this idea that we all should go to the sea resort because we must get our skin full of cancer.

00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:35.000
So the quality of a person doesn't depend on a mental acceptance of something that looks new.

00:33:35.000 --> 00:33:45.000
